# KisanVaani environment variables
# Copy to .env.local and fill in. Every variable is optional in the sense that
# the app degrades gracefully without it — but for full functionality set all.

# --- AI (required for live intelligence) -----------------------------------
# Google Gemini API key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey (free tier works;
# a billing-enabled project avoids daily quota throttles during demos).
# Without it: every AI route serves reviewed cached advisories.
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Optional model overrides (defaults shown).
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
# GEMINI_MODEL_FALLBACK=gemini-2.5-flash-lite

# --- Persistence (optional) ------------------------------------------------
# Any Postgres connection string (Neon recommended: https://neon.tech, free tier).
# Tables (kv_tickets, kv_broadcasts, kv_queries) are created automatically on
# first use. Without it: tickets/broadcasts/query-log fall back to per-instance
# memory — the app still runs, but the farmer→expert loop does not persist.
DATABASE_URL=

# --- Telephony (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
# Twilio credentials: https://console.twilio.com (trial account is sufficient).
# Enables webhook signature validation on /api/telephony/* and WhatsApp media
# download. Point your Twilio number's Voice/SMS webhooks at
#   https://<your-deployment>/api/telephony/voice  (POST)
#   https://<your-deployment>/api/telephony/sms    (POST)
# or run: node scripts/configure-twilio.mjs
# Without these: telephony endpoints skip signature validation (local dev mode).
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER=

# --- No keys needed ---------------------------------------------------------
# These live data sources are keyless and called directly by the server:
#   Open-Meteo (weather/soil moisture), ISRIC SoilGrids (satellite soil),
#   NASA POWER (agroclimate), Agmarknet 2.0 (mandi prices),
#   Soil Health Card GraphQL (soilhealth4.dac.gov.in).
